## üîß ADDING NEW COLORS

When adding new colors:

1. Add to appropriate category in `AppColors.swift`
2. Use `adaptiveColor(light:dark:)` for dark mode support
3. Document in this rule file
4. Use semantic naming (by purpose, not appearance)

```swift
// ‚úÖ Good: Named by purpose
static let cardBackground = adaptiveColor(light: "FFFFFF", dark: "1A1A1A")

// ‚ùå Bad: Named by appearance
static let whiteColor = Color(hex: "FFFFFF")
```

